I cannot believe it has taken me this long to write a review for Justina Duong's wonderful Cyclo Vietnames Cuisine.  We visited Cyclo for the first time on the first Friday after a very positive review by the Arizona Republic food critic Howard Seftel.  The small place was slammed.  Being a woman of action, I stepped in and helped by being the "hostess" and taking down names for a waiting list.  Guess that helped me become friends with the acerbic but deep down sweet woman that is Justina Duong.  You really can't go wrong with anything on the menu.  Spring rolls are compact but full of all sorts of meat and veggies.  Bun Hanoi and Bun Saigon are tasty treats full of fresh herbs and vegetables.  My husband loves this lemon chicken curry dish that to me smells like Lemon Pledge, but he gets it each time.   the beef pho is full of flavor and comes with a mound of salad, unlike some of the other "cheaper" pho shops nearby.    i can't imagine anyone has complaints with the food at Cyclo.  If they do, it is probably that their judgment is clouded as they came on a Friday and Saturday night at 7 p.m. to a 14 table establishment and expected to be served immediately and be fawned after.  If you are this needy, don't come here and take up a table...we're waiting patiently to be served. :)

